have hp pavilion dv laptop when trying to start it it does not start it freezes need help laptop kind of go into the freeze mode when it start you can see the window logo and when i tilt the base of laptop or apply pressure near the touch mouse on the laptop then it starts loading the operating system but sometimes it works fine i have run the recovery disk and loaded the software but it still gives me problem knowing that you have to tilt or apply pressure is a huge red flag chances are your laptop is physically damaged specifically the hard drive if it boots when you change the angle it means that the heads on the hard drive are likely faulty and failing the pressure problem may indicate a cracked board or peripheral i'm near willing to bet that your warranty has expired so you going to have to make a decision as to how to treat this problem three choices a new hard drive may do the trick b send it in for service this can be very pricey which brings me to c shop for a new affordable laptop with an extended warranty Hard disk IBM PC compatible Windows XP Computer virus Windows 2000 Apple Macintosh Mouse (computing) Personal computer Universal Serial Bus Laptop Redundant array of independent disks Booting Bluetooth AmigaOS Atari 8-bit family Computer forensics File system Atari ST Partition (computing) Floppy disk Apple Computer IBook IBM PC NeXT IPod DOS Virtual memory Apple II family Warranty Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis History of Microsoft Windows Apple IIGS Linux MS-DOS Desktop computer TRS-80 FreeDOS Xbox PlayStation 2 File Allocation Table Digital Equipment Corporation DR-DOS Embedded system Upper Memory Area Emulator X86 assembly language Copy protection Microsoft Windows Data recovery Computer hardware Overclocking ATI Technologies Mandriva Linux Trademark Timeline of computing 1990-forward Disk cloning Central processing unit Sega Dreamcast Kernel (computer science) Windows 3.x Computer bus Cray-1 PowerBook History of computing hardware (1960s-present) Pro